title: Terminally ill groom marries in stunning medieval ceremony
text: Terminally ill groom marries woman he met at school in stunning medieval ceremony after a charity gifted them a wedding so they can 'make memories' before he dies Roda Newberry and Damien Leask wed last Thursday at Sunshine Castle in Bli Bli Were gifted the $25,000 ceremony by not-for-profit charity My Wedding Wish Roda and Damien had been dating for a year when he popped the question Damien, who has cystic fibrosis, cannot get new set of lungs and has limited time His double transplant began to fail after he received radiation for cancer on lip Published: 03:08 GMT, 14 February 2017 | Updated: 03:11 GMT, 14 February 2017 113 shares
